title: Beet And Goat Cheese Salad With Baby Greens And Walnuts
summary: You can never have too many main course recipes, so give Beet And Goat Cheese Salad With Baby Greens And Walnuts a try. This recipe serves 3 and costs $3.59 per serving. One serving contains 538 calories, 14g of protein, and 47g of fat. This recipe from recipes.prevention.com has 1 fans. A mixture of baby greens, beets, olive oil, and a handful of other ingredients are all it takes to make this recipe so yummy. To use up the walnut oil you could follow this main course with the Walnut Chiffon Cake as a dessert. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes approximately 26 minutes. It is a good option if you're following a gluten free, primal, and vegetarian diet. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 64%. This score is pretty good. Similar recipes include Beet Risotto with Greens, Goat Cheese, and Walnuts, Beets with Walnuts, Goat Cheese, and Baby Greens, and Roasted Butternut Squash with Beet Greens, Goat Cheese, Toasted Walnuts and Mint.
